quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,53,"Say, \"O my servants! Who have acted extravagantly (transgressed) against their own souls, do not despair of the mercy of Allah; surely Allah forgives all faults; surely He is the Forgiving the Merciful"
  39,54,And return to your Lord time after time and submit to Him before there come unto you the punishment when you cannot be helped
  39,55,And follow the best of that which has been revealed to you from your Lord before the punishment comes suddenly while you do not even perceive
  39,56,"Lest a soul should say, \"O woe to me! For what I fell short of my duty to Allah, and I was indeed among the scoffers"
  39,57,"Or should say, \"Had Allah guided me, I would certainly have been of those who are dutiful"
  39,58,"Or should say when it sees the punishment, \"O, if I only had another chance that I might be among the righteous"
  39,59,"(But the answer will be,) \"Nay! For My revelations came to you, but you rejected them, and were haughty and you were among the unbelievers"
  39,60,And on the Day of Resurrection you shall see those who lied against Allah; their faces shall be blackened. Is there not in hell an abode for the haughty
  39,61,"And Allah shall deliver those who guard (against evil) with their achievement; evil shall not touch them, nor shall they grieve"
  39,62,Allah is the Creator of all things and He is the Guardian and Disposer of all things
  39,63,"His are the keys of the heavens and the earth; and those who disbelieve in the revelations of Allah, these it is that are the losers"